						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Vyaya</hi></p>						

						<p>Refers to a <hi rend="italic">muṟi</hi> (document of agreement) by the Śrī Bāgapada(Bhāgavata) nambimār agreeing to offer garlands of various flowers or to pay fine in default to god Raṅganātha. The details of the date viz., <hi rend="bold">Viya (Vyaya), Kārttigai 28</hi> are not enough for verification. In characters of the 16th century A.D. <hi rend="bold">Vyaya</hi> falling in this period may correspond to <hi rend="bold">1526 A.D.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
